  "abstract": "The objective of this investigation was to examine the effects of one generation\r\nof selfing on grain yield, plant height, head length, 1000 seed weight, and days to\r\nflowering in the base populations as well as in three successive full sib recurrem\r\nselection cycle bulks of the Medium Maturity Composite and Serere Composite-l of\r\npearl millet -[Penniseium americanum (L.) Leeke). The experimental materials consisted\r\nof random mated bulks · and single generation selfed bulks from 400 random\r\npl~nts corresponding to each cycle (cycle 0 to 3) of both the composites. Results\r\nshowed that a.verage inbreeding depressions in both the composites were highest for\r\ngrain yield (25 % and 36 %) followed by 1000 seed weight (L2 % and 14 0/0). Plant height,days to flowering and --head length were least affected...............",
